crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a backdoor/bot that communicates with a Command and Control (C2) server over HTTP. It can execute remote commands via `cmd.exe /c`, capture the output, and dynamically load and execute code from DLLs (`rundll` command). It establishes persistence via a registry Run key with the value name 'WUpdate'. Before C2 communication, it performs reconnaissance by reading proxy settings from both Internet Explorer (registry) and Firefox (`prefs.js`). C2 communication uses a distinct URL pattern `/%x/ketwer90o/%02d%02d%02d%02d.html` and a hardcoded User-Agent `Mozilla/4.0 (compatible; MSIE 8.0; Win32)`.
